headline.main: Robert Frost Dies at 88; Kennedy Leads in Tribute; Poet Won Four Pulitzer Prizes--Took Part in 1961 Inauguration Robert Frost, Four-Time Winner of the Pulitzer Prize, Dies in Boston at Age of 88 POET WAS SYMBOL OF INDIVIDUALITY Work Rejected at First, He Later Moved Among World Leaders Funeral Tomorrow Remarkable in Many Ways Inauguration Incident Echoes the Poet's Cry 20 Years of Rejection Won Many Honors

snippet: BOSTON, Jan. 29 -- Robert Frost, dean of American poets, died today at the age of 88.
